{
  "video_id": "DtmAw9Ia7LA",
  "title": "Fallacies: Slippery Slope",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 950.0,
      "end_time": 2410.0,
      "text": "SPEAKER 1: The last content fallacy"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 2410.0,
      "end_time": 6500.0,
      "text": "that we&#39;re going to look at is slippery slope."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 6500.0,
      "end_time": 9895.0,
      "text": "Here&#39;s a pretty extreme example of a slippery slope fallacy."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 9895.0,
      "end_time": 13730.0,
      "text": "A high school kid&#39;s mom insists that she study on Saturdays."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 13730.0,
      "end_time": 14650.0,
      "text": "Why?"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 14650.0,
      "end_time": 16400.0,
      "text": "Because if she doesn&#39;t study on Saturdays,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 16400.0,
      "end_time": 19990.0,
      "text": "her grades will suffer, and she won&#39;t graduate high school"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 19100.0,
      "end_time": 20540.0,
      "text": "with honors."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 20540.0,
      "end_time": 21720.0,
      "text": "And if she doesn&#39;t graduate with honors,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 21720.0,
      "end_time": 23761.0,
      "text": "then she won&#39;t be able to get into the university"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 23761.0,
      "end_time": 24849.0,
      "text": "of her choice."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 24850.0,
      "end_time": 27547.0,
      "text": "And, well, the rest isn&#39;t clear, but the result of all this"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 27547.0,
      "end_time": 29130.0,
      "text": "is that she&#39;ll end up flipping burgers"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 29130.0,
      "end_time": 30439.0,
      "text": "for the rest of her life."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 30440.0,
      "end_time": 32299.0,
      "text": "And surely, she doesn&#39;t want that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 32299.0,
      "end_time": 35400.0,
      "text": "so she better darn well get serious and study."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 35400.0,
      "end_time": 37930.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ve actually heard a version of this discussion between two"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 37930.0,
      "end_time": 40180.0,
      "text": "wealthy mothers who were talking about which preschool"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 40180.0,
      "end_time": 41464.0,
      "text": "to send their kids to."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 41464.0,
      "end_time": 43379.0,
      "text": "The gist was that if they didn&#39;t get their kid"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 43380.0,
      "end_time": 44916.0,
      "text": "into a prestigious preschool, then"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 44916.0,
      "end_time": 46540.0,
      "text": "they&#39;d be disadvantaged from that point"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 46540.0,
      "end_time": 48870.0,
      "text": "forward in ways that could ultimately threaten"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 48870.0,
      "end_time": 51300.0,
      "text": "their future life prospects."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 51300.0,
      "end_time": 54660.0,
      "text": "So this was not a decision to be taken lightly."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 54660.0,
      "end_time": 57930.0,
      "text": "I did not envy those kids."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 57930.0,
      "end_time": 61570.0,
      "text": "Here&#39;s the schematic form of a slippery slope argument."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 61570.0,
      "end_time": 64239.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a series of connected conditional claims"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 64239.00000000001,
      "end_time": 66580.0,
      "text": "to the effect that if you assume that A is true"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 66580.0,
      "end_time": 69480.0,
      "text": "or allow A to occur, then B will follow."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 69480.0,
      "end_time": 72540.0,
      "text": "And if B follows, then C will follow, and if C follows,"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 72540.0,
      "end_time": 74380.0,
      "text": "then D will follow."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 74380.0,
      "end_time": 77681.0,
      "text": "But D is something nasty that we all want to avoid."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 77681.0,
      "end_time": 79679.0,
      "text": "So the conclusion is that if we want to avoid D,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 79680.0,
      "end_time": 84130.0,
      "text": "we need to reject A, or not allow A to happen."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 84130.0,
      "end_time": 87690.0,
      "text": "Now, note that as stated, the logic of this argument is fine."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 87690.0,
      "end_time": 89380.0,
      "text": "In fact, this is a valid argument form"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 89380.0,
      "end_time": 90929.0,
      "text": "that we&#39;ve seen before."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 90930.0,
      "end_time": 92690.0,
      "text": "We&#39;ve called it hypothetical syllogism,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 92690.0,
      "end_time": 96730.0,
      "text": "or reasoning in a chain with conditionals."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 96730.0,
      "end_time": 99290.0,
      "text": "Slippery slopes are fallacious only if the premises"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 99290.0,
      "end_time": 101900.0,
      "text": "are false or implausible."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 101900.0,
      "end_time": 103610.0,
      "text": "Everything turns on whether these conditional relationships"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 103610.0,
      "end_time": 104600.0,
      "text": "hold."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 104600.0,
      "end_time": 105649.0,
      "text": "Sometimes, they do."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 105650.0,
      "end_time": 108540.0,
      "text": "And if they do, it&#39;s not a fallacy."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 108540.0,
      "end_time": 109920.0,
      "text": "But very often, they don&#39;t."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 109920.0,
      "end_time": 112730.0,
      "text": "And when they don&#39;t, we&#39;ve got a slippery slope fallacy."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 112730.0,
      "end_time": 114360.0,
      "text": "Now, there&#39;s a caveat to this way"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 114360.0,
      "end_time": 116736.0,
      "text": "of analyzing slippery slopes."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 116736.0,
      "end_time": 118860.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s usually the case that slippery slope arguments"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 118860.0,
      "end_time": 122480.0,
      "text": "aren&#39;t intended to be valid-- that is, they&#39;re not intended"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 122480.0,
      "end_time": 124860.0,
      "text": "to establish that the dreaded consequence will follow"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 124860.0,
      "end_time": 126910.0,
      "text": "with absolute certainty."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 126910.0,
      "end_time": 129710.0,
      "text": "Usually the intent is to argue that if you assume A,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 129710.00000000001,
      "end_time": 131770.0,
      "text": "then D is very likely to follow."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 131770.0,
      "end_time": 135184.0,
      "text": "So what&#39;s being aimed for is really a strong argument."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 135184.0,
      "end_time": 136600.0,
      "text": "And that means we shouldn&#39;t really"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 136600.0,
      "end_time": 139680.0,
      "text": "be reading the conditional claims as strict conditionals"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 139680.0,
      "end_time": 141310.0,
      "text": "with every link in the chain following"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 141310.0,
      "end_time": 143570.0,
      "text": "with absolute necessity."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 143570.0,
      "end_time": 145870.0,
      "text": "We should be asking ourselves, how likely is it"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 145870.0,
      "end_time": 148440.0,
      "text": "that D will follow if A occurs?"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 148440.0,
      "end_time": 151430.0,
      "text": "If it&#39;s very likely, then the logic is strong."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 151430.0,
      "end_time": 153310.0,
      "text": "If not, then it&#39;s weak."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 153310.0,
      "end_time": 156390.0,
      "text": "So in a sense, we&#39;re evaluating the logic of the argument."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 156390.0,
      "end_time": 158140.0,
      "text": "But it turns out that in cases like this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 158140.0,
      "end_time": 162190.0,
      "text": "the strength of the logic turns on the content of the premises."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 162200.0,
      "end_time": 164800.0,
      "text": "So in the end, we are evaluating the plausibility"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 164800.0,
      "end_time": 167620.0,
      "text": "of premises, which makes this a content fallacy, and not"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 167620.0,
      "end_time": 170880.0,
      "text": "a logical or formal fallacy."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 170880.0,
      "end_time": 174260.0,
      "text": "For our example, the chain of inferences looks like this."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 174260.0,
      "end_time": 177310.0,
      "text": "Now, this argument is obviously bad at every stage"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 177310.0,
      "end_time": 179110.0,
      "text": "of the reasoning."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 179110.0,
      "end_time": 181260.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s possible that not studying on Saturdays"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 181260.0,
      "end_time": 183440.0,
      "text": "could make a difference to whether the student gets"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 183440.0,
      "end_time": 185190.0,
      "text": "on the honor roll, but there&#39;s no evidence"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 185190.0,
      "end_time": 187160.0,
      "text": "that this is likely."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 187160.0,
      "end_time": 188920.0,
      "text": "Yes, if you&#39;re not on the honor roll, then"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 188920.0,
      "end_time": 190459.0,
      "text": "maybe this will affect your chances"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 190460.0,
      "end_time": 193250.0,
      "text": "of getting into a top university."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 193250.0,
      "end_time": 196260.0,
      "text": "But without specifying what counts as a top university,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 196260.0,
      "end_time": 197400.0,
      "text": "one of the factors may or may not"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 197400.0,
      "end_time": 200390.0,
      "text": "be operating-- like, for example, whether the student is"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 200390.0,
      "end_time": 201875.0,
      "text": "a minority or an athlete."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 201875.0,
      "end_time": 205900.0,
      "text": "They might be eligible for non-academic scholarships"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 205900.0,
      "end_time": 206900.0,
      "text": "of various kinds."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 206900.0,
      "end_time": 211540.0,
      "text": "Then it&#39;s impossible to assess the chances in this case."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 211540.0,
      "end_time": 214750.0,
      "text": "The last move, from failing to get into a top university"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 214750.0,
      "end_time": 216250.0,
      "text": "to flipping burgers for a living,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 216250.0,
      "end_time": 219230.0,
      "text": "is obviously the weakest link in the chain."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 219230.0,
      "end_time": 222239.0,
      "text": "This is just widely pessimistic speculation with nothing"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 222240.0,
      "end_time": 223430.0,
      "text": "to support it."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 223430.0,
      "end_time": 226760.0,
      "text": "So each link in the chain is weak, and the chain as a whole"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 226760.0,
      "end_time": 229720.0,
      "text": "simply compounds those weaknesses."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 229720.0,
      "end_time": 232540.0,
      "text": "By saying this, we&#39;re saying that premises 1, 2, and 3 are"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 232540.0,
      "end_time": 234799.0,
      "text": "not plausible, and so the inference from A to D"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 234800.0,
      "end_time": 236730.0,
      "text": "is not possible."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 236730.0,
      "end_time": 240154.0,
      "text": "We have no reason to think that this slope is not slippery."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 240154.0,
      "end_time": 242320.0,
      "text": "Now, there&#39;s another obvious way that one can attack"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 242320.0,
      "end_time": 243489.0,
      "text": "a slippery slope argument."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 243490.0,
      "end_time": 246400.0,
      "text": "You might be willing to grant that the slope is slippery"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 246400.0,
      "end_time": 248860.0,
      "text": "but deny that what awaits at the bottom of the slope"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 248860.0,
      "end_time": 251250.0,
      "text": "is really all that bad."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 251250.0,
      "end_time": 253200.0,
      "text": "This would be to challenge premise 4,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 253200.0,
      "end_time": 257400.0,
      "text": "the not D. Not D says that D is objectionable in some way,"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 257399.99999999997,
      "end_time": 260109.99999999997,
      "text": "that we don&#39;t want to accept D. But this"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 260110.0,
      "end_time": 261832.0,
      "text": "might be open to debate."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 261832.0,
      "end_time": 263290.0,
      "text": "Put away to the bottom of the slope"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 263290.0,
      "end_time": 265640.0,
      "text": "is \"and\" then you die a painful death,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 265640.0,
      "end_time": 268287.0,
      "text": "or \"and then all our civil rights are taken away.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 268287.0,
      "end_time": 269870.0,
      "text": "And sure, just about everyone is going"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 269870.0,
      "end_time": 271809.0,
      "text": "to agree that that&#39;s a bad outcome."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 271809.0,
      "end_time": 273350.0,
      "text": "But it&#39;s not as obvious that everyone"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 273350.0,
      "end_time": 276140.0,
      "text": "will find flipping burgers objectionable,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 276140.0,
      "end_time": 278620.0,
      "text": "or whatever this notion stands for-- working in the service"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 278620.0,
      "end_time": 282100.0,
      "text": "industry, or working in a low-paying job or whatever."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 282100.0,
      "end_time": 284580.0,
      "text": "What&#39;s important in evaluating a slippery slope argument"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 284580.0,
      "end_time": 286909.0,
      "text": "is that the intended audience of the argument"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 286910.0,
      "end_time": 290400.0,
      "text": "finds the bottom of the slope objectionable."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 290400.0,
      "end_time": 292170.0,
      "text": "So this is another way to criticize a slippery slope"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 292170.0,
      "end_time": 295360.0,
      "text": "argument-- by arguing that the outcome of this chain of events"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 295360.0,
      "end_time": 297850.0,
      "text": "really isn&#39;t as objectionable as the arguer would"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 297850.0,
      "end_time": 300370.0,
      "text": "like you to think."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 300370.0,
      "end_time": 302267.0,
      "text": "So just to summarize what we&#39;ve said so far--"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 302267.0,
      "end_time": 304350.0,
      "text": "there are two ways of challenging a slippery slope"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 304350.0,
      "end_time": 304970.0,
      "text": "argument."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 304970.0,
      "end_time": 306810.0,
      "text": "The first one is to challenge the strength"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 306810.0,
      "end_time": 310319.0,
      "text": "of the conditional relationships that the argument relies on."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 310319.0,
      "end_time": 312860.0,
      "text": "When people say that a slippery slope argument is fallacious,"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 312860.0,
      "end_time": 315869.0,
      "text": "they usually mean that the chain of inferences is weak."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 315869.0,
      "end_time": 317910.0,
      "text": "By the way, I hope it&#39;s clear that slippery slope"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 317910.0,
      "end_time": 320360.0,
      "text": "arguments don&#39;t have to have only three links."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 320360.0,
      "end_time": 323560.0,
      "text": "My argument schema could&#39;ve been longer or shorter."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 323560.0,
      "end_time": 325800.0,
      "text": "Now, second, you can also challenge a slippery slope"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 325800.0,
      "end_time": 328770.0,
      "text": "argument by challenging the objectionableness of whatever"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 328770.0,
      "end_time": 330710.0,
      "text": "lies at the end of the chain."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 330710.0,
      "end_time": 333000.0,
      "text": "If it&#39;s not obvious to the intended audience"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 333000.0,
      "end_time": 335600.0,
      "text": "that this is actually a bad thing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 335600.0,
      "end_time": 337640.0,
      "text": "then the argument will fail to persuade, regardless of how"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 337640.0,
      "end_time": 339919.0,
      "text": "slippery the slope may be."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 339919.0,
      "end_time": 341960.0,
      "text": "Before wrapping up, I&#39;d like to make a few points"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 341960.0,
      "end_time": 346111.0,
      "text": "about assessing the plausibility of conditional chains."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 346112.0,
      "end_time": 347570.0,
      "text": "Fallacious slippery slope arguments"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 347570.0,
      "end_time": 350990.0,
      "text": "often succeeded at persuading their audience"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 350100.0,
      "end_time": 351990.0,
      "text": "because people misjudge the strength"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 351990.0,
      "end_time": 354500.0,
      "text": "of the chain of inferences."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 354500.0,
      "end_time": 356470.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re prone to thinking that the chain is stronger"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 356470.0,
      "end_time": 357990.0,
      "text": "than it actually is."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 357990.0,
      "end_time": 360000.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s important to realize two things."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 360000.0,
      "end_time": 362310.0,
      "text": "First, a chain of conditional inferences"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 362310.0,
      "end_time": 364820.0,
      "text": "is only as strong as its weakest link."
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 364820.0,
      "end_time": 366810.0,
      "text": "The weakest conditional claim-- the one that"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 366810.0,
      "end_time": 370280.0,
      "text": "is least likely to be true-- is the one that sets the upper"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 370280.0,
      "end_time": 373234.0,
      "text": "bound on the strength of the chain as a whole."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 373234.0,
      "end_time": 375150.0,
      "text": "So even if some of the inferences in the chain"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 375150.0,
      "end_time": 377530.0,
      "text": "are plausible, the chain itself is only"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 377530.0,
      "end_time": 380200.0,
      "text": "as strong as the weakest inference."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 380200.0,
      "end_time": 383654.0,
      "text": "Second, weaknesses in the links have a compounding effect,"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 383654.0,
      "end_time": 385700.0,
      "text": "so the strength of the whole chain"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 385700.0,
      "end_time": 388694.0,
      "text": "is almost always much weaker than the weakest link."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 388694.0,
      "end_time": 391110.0,
      "text": "To see why this is so, you can think of conditional claims"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 391110.0,
      "end_time": 393530.0,
      "text": "as probabilistic inferences."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 393530.0,
      "end_time": 396460.0,
      "text": "If A is true, then B follows with some probability,"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 396460.0,
      "end_time": 398930.0,
      "text": "and this probability is usually less than one,"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 398930.0,
      "end_time": 401510.0,
      "text": "or less than 100%."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 401510.0,
      "end_time": 403180.0,
      "text": "So the probability of D following"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 403180.0,
      "end_time": 406340.0,
      "text": "from A, the probability of the whole inference,"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 406340.0,
      "end_time": 409900.0,
      "text": "is actually a multiplicative product"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 409900.0,
      "end_time": 412840.0,
      "text": "of the probabilities of each of the individual links."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 412840.0,
      "end_time": 415900.0,
      "text": "Now, the odds of a coin landing heads on a single toss"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 415900.0,
      "end_time": 418130.0,
      "text": "is one half, or 50%."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 418130.0,
      "end_time": 419730.0,
      "text": "The odds of a coin landing heads twice"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 419730.0,
      "end_time": 423160.0,
      "text": "in a row is one half times one half, or one quarter,"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 423160.0,
      "end_time": 425150.0,
      "text": "which is 25%."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 425150.0,
      "end_time": 428770.0,
      "text": "Conditional inferences compound in a similar way."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 428770.0,
      "end_time": 431159.0,
      "text": "So if the odds for each link in the chain were,"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 431160.0,
      "end_time": 434860.0,
      "text": "let&#39;s say, 90%, then the odds of the whole chain being true,"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 434860.0,
      "end_time": 440649.0,
      "text": "of D actually following from A, would only be 0.73, or 73%,"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 440649.0,
      "end_time": 442190.0,
      "text": "and this number would go down further"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 442190.0,
      "end_time": 444850.0,
      "text": "with each additional link in the chain."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 444850.0,
      "end_time": 446950.0,
      "text": "People in general are very bad at estimating"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 446950.0,
      "end_time": 451100.0,
      "text": "compound probabilities and will tend to overestimate them."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 451100.0,
      "end_time": 452750.0,
      "text": "Here&#39;s the calculation if one of the links"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 452750.0,
      "end_time": 457400.0,
      "text": "is weaker than the rest-- say, 0.6, or 60%."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 457400.0,
      "end_time": 458750.0,
      "text": "The probability of D following from A"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 458750.0,
      "end_time": 463400.0,
      "text": "actually drops below 50%, a very weak inference."
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 463400.0,
      "end_time": 466669.0,
      "text": "But very few people will read the probabilities this way."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 466670.0,
      "end_time": 469400.0,
      "text": "Their attention will focus on the highly probable bits"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 469400.0,
      "end_time": 471520.0,
      "text": "of the story, and their estimate of the overall odds"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 471520.0,
      "end_time": 474370.0,
      "text": "will be anchored to these bits, especially if they&#39;re"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 474370.0,
      "end_time": 476850.0,
      "text": "either at the very beginning or the very end of the chain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 476850.0,
      "end_time": 479270.0,
      "text": "since these make the biggest impression."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 479270.0,
      "end_time": 481409.0,
      "text": "So human beings in general are quite"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 481410.0,
      "end_time": 483846.0,
      "text": "vulnerable to slippery slope reasoning,"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 483846.0,
      "end_time": 485470.0,
      "text": "and knowing these facts should motivate"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 485470.0,
      "end_time": 487220.0,
      "text": "you to be more critical when you encounter"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 487220.0,
      "end_time": 489220.0,
      "text": "these kinds of arguments."
    }
  ]
}